2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper focuses on the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning.
3. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper discusses the use of Nash equilibrium in poker gameplay, which is a concept from game theory.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses deep neural networks to improve the performance of the poker-playing algorithm, making cs.NE a likely sub-category.
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - Although the paper does not directly deal with computer vision or pattern recognition, the use of deep neural networks is a common technique in these fields, making cs.CV a possible sub-category.
